{"lemma":"ذِمَّةٌ","slug":"ذِمَّةٌ","root":"ذ.م.م","root_slug":"ذ-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ذِمَّة","root":"ذمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14021"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%90%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"peace, custody, guardianship, care"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"responsibility, liability, blame","examples":[{"text":"هذه القاعدة فرع عن قاعدة \"اليقين لا يزول بالشك\" (م/ ٤)؛ لأن اليقين لا يزول إلا بيقين مثله، ولأن اليقين ثابت فلا يلغى إلا بمثله، ومن ذلك إذا شغلت الذمة بيقين في مقتضى حكم شرعي، أو بحق من الحقوق، فلا تبرأ من ذلك إلا بيقين يثبت براءة الذمة","english":"This rule is a branch of the rule \"Certainty is not removed by doubt\" (Islamic jurisprudential maxim 4). Because certainty is only removed by an equal certainty, and because certainty is established, it is not nullified except by its equivalent. Therefore, if liability is established with certainty in a legal judgment or in a matter related to rights, it cannot be absolved except by an equal certainty that proves the exoneration of liability."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ðim.ma/","/zim.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14021","headword_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ","root":"*m","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A compact, a covenant, a contract, a league, a treaty, an engagement, a bond,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an obligation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K;) because the breaking thereof necessitates blame: (Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~N","text_ar":"حَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the neglect of which one is to be blamed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in ix. 8:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an inviolable right"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*imaAmN","text_ar":"ذِمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*im~apN","text_ar":"مَذِمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*am~apN","text_ar":"مَذَمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify in like manner"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a compact, a covenant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the neglect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nonobservance, of which a man is to be blamed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or these three words [in the CK the first and last only] signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~N","text_ar":"حَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or so the first of them: (T, * S:) and each of them, (M, K,) or the first of them, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*imaAmN","text_ar":"ذِمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which includes all the significations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise, those above and those which follow, but appears here to be used as meaning especially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that should be sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which one is under an obligation to reverence, respect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour, and defend; everything that is entitled to reverence, respect, honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defence. in the character and appertenances"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a person]; (S, M, Mgh, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huromap","text_ar":"حُرْمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the neglect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"non-observance, of which one is to be blamed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*amaAmapN","text_ar":"ذَمَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*imaAmapN","text_ar":"ذِمَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~N","text_ar":"حَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaAnN","text_ar":"اَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"security,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safety; security of life and property; protection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safeguard; a promise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an assurance, of security, safety, protection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safeguard; indemnity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Mgh, Msb, KL, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*imaAmN","text_ar":"ذِمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MA, KL: [explained in both by the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinohaAro","text_ar":"زِنْهَارْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the latter by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~N","text_ar":"حَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also:]) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"responsibility"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the fulfilment of an obligation, for the payment of a sum of money, for the restitution of a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the safety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safe-keeping, of a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suretiship;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*amaAmapN","text_ar":"ذَمَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*imaAmapN","text_ar":"ذِمَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K; [in the former of which, these two words are said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in all the senses mentioned above;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~N","text_ar":"ذِمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K: [said in the M to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the first"},{"kind":"text","text":"only"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the senses mentioned above in this paragraph:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAl*~im~u","text_ar":"والذِّمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa Al*~im~i","text_ar":"وَ الذِّمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*imamN","text_ar":"ذِمَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*imaAmN","text_ar":"ذِمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*imaAmN","text_ar":"ذِمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as [a sing.] syn. with ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*am~apN","text_ar":"مَذَمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*im~apN","text_ar":"مَذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*im~apN","text_ar":"اَذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) Hence, i. e. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first of the senses explained above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahlu Al*~im~api","text_ar":"اَهلُ الذِّمَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, TA.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~im~ipu","text_ar":"الذِّمِّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, * Mgh, K, TA,) with the prefixed noun"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ahl","text_ar":"اهل"},{"kind":"text","text":"suppressed, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people with whom a compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has been made;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K, TA;) [and particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those, of the believers in a plurality of Gods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by which are here meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Christians, Jews, and Sabians,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but no others,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who pay the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tax called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizoyap","text_ar":"جِزْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, TA;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the free non-Muslim subjects of a Muslim government, who pay a poll-tax for which the Muslims are responsible for their security and freedom and toleration:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholN","text_ar":"اَهْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the appellation ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~iY~N","text_ar":"ذِمِّىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) a rel. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~im~apu","text_ar":"الذِّمَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb;) is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person of this class;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) because he is rendered secure, or free from fear, for his property and his blood, by means of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizoyap","text_ar":"جِزْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEala Eumaru A^ahola Als~awaAdi *im~apF","text_ar":"جَعَلَ عُمَرُ اَهْلَ السَّوَادِ ذِمَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"'Omar treated"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of the Sawád as those who are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu Al*~im~api","text_ar":"اَهْلُ الذِّمَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqobilonaA bi*im~apK","text_ar":"اَقْبِلْنَا بِذِمَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqolibonaA","text_ar":"اَقْلِبْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"?], in the prayer of the traveller, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Restore us to our family in safety."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is related in a trad. of 'Alee, that he said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~atiY bimaA","text_ar":"ذِمَّتِى بِمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aquwlu rahiynapN wa A^anaA bihi zaEiymN","text_ar":"اَقُولُ رَهِينَةٌ وَ اَنَا بِهِ زَعِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My responsibility is pledged for"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the truth of]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what I say, and I am answerable for it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA; *) i. e. this my saying is true, and I am responsible for it. (Mgh.) And it is said in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqado","text_ar":"فَقَدْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^ato minohu Al*~im~ap","text_ar":"بَرِيَتْ مِنْهُ الذِّمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then the responsibility"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit, of him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e. there is given to every one, by God, a covenant whereby He binds Himself to preserve and protect him; and when he throws himself into destruction, or does that which is unlawful for him to do, or acts at variance with that which he is commanded to do, the covenant of God fails to aid him. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY *im~atiY ka*aA","text_ar":"فِى ذِمَّتِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY DamaAniY","text_ar":"فى ضَمَانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[virtually"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am responsible for such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. for paying it, or restoring it, &c.; but lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in my responsibility is such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on my responsibility rests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be, such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be here used, as it is in many other instances, in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) [or,] in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vabata fiY *im~atiY ka*aA","text_ar":"ثَبَتَ فِى ذِمَّتِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a thing became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become, binding, obligatory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incumbent, on me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~ap","text_ar":"ذِمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to designate [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moral sense considered as"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seat"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sense"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of obligation to fulfil what is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"properly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~ap","text_ar":"ذِمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aDaAEi","text_ar":"الرَّضَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yu*ohibu Ean~iY ma*im~apa","text_ar":"مَا يُذْهِبُ عَنِّى مَذِمَّةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh, *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aDaAEi","text_ar":"الرَّضَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*am~apa","text_ar":"مَذَمَّةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Mgh,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What will put away from me the obligation of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the woman who has suckled"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the sucking?"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a question occurring in a trad., (T, S, Mgh, *) as put by a man to the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":977},{"kind":"text","text":"Prophet: (T:) and the answer was, “ A slave, male or female: ” (T, S, Mgh:) En-Nakha'ee says, (S,) they liked, on the occasion of the weaning of a child, to give the woman who had suckled it something beside the hire: (S, Mgh:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*am~apN","text_ar":"مَذَمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this case is a dial. var. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*im~apN","text_ar":"مَذِمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) or, as IAth says, the former is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~am~u","text_ar":"الذَّمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the latter, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~im~ahu","text_ar":"الذِّمَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aDaAEi bi$~aYo'K tuEoTiyhi","text_ar":"الرَّضَاعِ بِشَّىْءٍ تُعْطِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*ohibo Eanoka ma*am~a","text_ar":"اَذْهِبْ عَنْكَ مَذَمَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~iy^ora","text_ar":"الظِّيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aDaAEi","text_ar":"الرَّضَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*im~a","text_ar":"مَذِمَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Put away from thee the obligation of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is incumbent on thee to render her"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the sucking"},{"kind":"text","text":"of thy child ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by something that thou shalt give to her who has suckled"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*ohibo Eanoka","text_ar":"اَذْهِبْ عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aYo'K","text_ar":"بِشَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*im~atahumo","text_ar":"مَذِمَّتَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*am~atahumo","text_ar":"مَذَمَّتَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, and so accord. to different copies of the S and K, in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Enk","text_ar":"عنك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is omitted,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*am~ap","text_ar":"مَذَمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a dial. var., (T,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Put away from thee the obligation of their right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, by something;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feed them with something,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"give to them something,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for they have a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDaY ma*im~atahu","text_ar":"قَضَى مَذِمَّتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*am~atahu","text_ar":"مَذَمَّتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He paid his right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did good to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conferred upon him a benefit"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefits, in order that he might not be blamed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw ma*im~apK","text_ar":"ذُو مَذِمَّةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*am~apK","text_ar":"مَذَمَّةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK the latter only,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who has a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~N","text_ar":"كَلٌّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"عَلَى النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man who is a burden upon people, to be maintained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supported, by them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K, TA.)       -A2-  Also (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A repast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"banquet, to which guests are invited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"simply"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a wedding."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*am~apN","text_ar":"ذَمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","M","K","T","S","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}